sequenceDiagram
    participant K as svc_handler
    participant CS as context_switch.S
    participant T as svc_exit_trampoline
    participant H as Hardware
    participant U as User Task

    Note over K: Task Switch Decision
    K->>CS: context_switch(prev, next)
    activate CS
    
    Note over CS: 1. Save PREV (User A)
    CS->>CS: stmfd sp!, {r4-r11, lr} (Callee-Saved)
    
    rect rgb(200, 255, 200)
    Note right of CS: Access User Banked Regs
    CS->>H: cps #0x1F (SYSTEM Mode)
    H->>CS: str sp, [prev->sp_usr] (Save SP_usr)
    H->>CS: str lr, [prev->lr_usr] (Save LR_usr)
    CS->>H: cps #0x13 (SVC Mode)
    end
    
    Note over CS: 2. Load NEXT (User B)
    CS->>CS: ldmia [next->sp_svc] (Switch Kernel Stack)
    
    rect rgb(200, 255, 200)
    Note right of CS: Restore User Banked Regs
    CS->>H: cps #0x1F (SYSTEM Mode)
    H->>CS: ldr sp, [next->sp_usr] (Restore SP_usr)
    H->>CS: ldr lr, [next->lr_usr] (Restore LR_usr)
    CS->>H: cps #0x13 (SVC Mode)
    end
    
    CS->>K: return (to new task's handler)
    deactivate CS
    
    Note over K: Finish Syscall
    K->>T: return result
    
    activate T
    Note over T: Trampoline
    T->>T: ldmfd sp!, {r0, r1} (Pop SPSR)
    T->>H: msr spsr, r0
    
    Note right of T: SP_usr already fixed by context_switch
    
    T->>U: ldmfd sp!, {r0-r12, pc}^
    deactivate T
    
    Note over U: Resume User B
